{
  "text": "-Patients with controlled and uncontrolled symptoms were estimated to lose 5.1 and 8.2 hours from work per week, respectively. [CITATION_1] -Employers were assumed to bear all the costs for absenteeism and 32% of the costs for presenteeism, as employees are present at work but not functioning at 100% capacity. [CITATION_2] -Using asthma exacerbations as a proxy measurement for symptom control, a 1% increase in compliance leads to a 0.44% increase in controlled asthma. [CITATION_3] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22888912",
    "[CITATION_2]": "40214857",
